comment.body:
@cothan I generally think that only the most performance or security sensitive routines should be replaced by assembly -- it is an overhead in terms of work, verification and maintenance.

Have you measured the relative performance of `poly_frommsg` and `poly_tomsg` in the overall context of MLKEM?

As for porting https://github.com/pq-crystals/kyber/commit/9b8d30698a3e7449aeb34e62339d4176f11e3c6c, I'd be more inclined to have a small library of constant-time stubs like `cmov_int16` so we can be sure that the compiler does not fiddle with it.

@mkannwischer What are your thoughts?
